James Robarge , 45, of Vermont was sentenced in court on Friday for second-degree murder in the death of his wife Kelly Robarge, 42 . 
  She disappeared from her home on June 27, 2013 and her body was found 10 days later with her hands and head detached . 
  Robarge has served nearly two years behind bars and could be eligible for parole in about 28 years . 
  Kelly's brother told Robarge he hoped he 'rotted in hell'